				mage pets do get alot better at 44. A magician can solo a sand giant at about level 37 I don't recommend it unless you have a few buffs on because most of the time your pet will die before the giant does. at 39 solo giants is fairly easy when using the fire pet.The fire pet will do the most damage while it is alive, heal the pet once when he is about half life(if you continue to heal him your just wasting mana) before and after the heal you should be nuking as fast as possible without drawing the aggro. most of the time your pet will die but when he does the giant should either be running or about to run. I also have a little to put in on the necro Vs. mage argument. necro's do get DoT's but so do mages, it may not be till about level 50 but when you are dueling you want to do as much damage as fast as possible. That means that DoT's don't help much, and with the new luclin spells a mage can outnuke a wizard if using the bracelet. If you know how to play your mage right you should be able to beat most necro's your level, one thing is you attack first by sending the pet after the necro not the necro's pet. this way the necro pet automatically goes for your pet, the necro will try and cast but with a pet hitting you its a little hard in most cases the necro pet will have to taunt your pet off before the necro can cast this tends to take a while most of the time. while the necro and his/her pet are busy with the mage pet the mage is free to nuke, leaving the necro to die a quick death.<BR>
<BR>
